reviews.review_text: Just had an Oreo McFlurry from here. Pretty good! Have you seen the prices of Dairy Queen blizzards lately? Its outrageous! You can make a decent argument in the difference of size between a regular McFlurry and a medium blizzard, bit of a battle right? But pound for pound and buck for buck, youre going to want to go for the Oreo McFlurry over the Oreo Blizzard, especially because I went around 10:45pm. Dairy Queen closes at like 9:00pm. Crazy! Everybody knows soft serve cream hits different post 10:00pm. This McDonalds experience has brought me happiness and they have gained a loyal customer over their opponent. Cheers.

Nice dual lane drive through McDonald s. Generally a quick and pleasant experience. Food is consistently fresh and accurate. Team is quick and precise. Large parking for convenient parking.  Today s order was an iced Frappuccino, 6 piece McNuggets, with a ranch snack wrap. My semi healthy post Coquitlam Crunch dinner (balance is key! Lol).

Here s my opinion of McDonalds. It s the same wherever I have been. The food is always good and the service is excellent. Some fast food places don t put napkins in the bag. McDonalds always does. It s simply a well run organization  .
Drove through with friends. They were pretty quick. Food was warm and tasted good

Good drive-thru service at this location this morning. I had issues with my app order code and was inadvertently holding up the line. The gentleman at the window was patient and professional in how he helped me, managing to track down the order successfully. The lady who delivered to my car window did so with a smile. They were very helpful in figuring it out, just wanted to say thanks!
Typical McDonalds. Had to wait a while for drive through food. Half of the car had eaten already when the rest of the food came.

This is specially for General manager (Mina). I have talked to you multiple times due to very bad management that I faced in your store, but today I wanted to congratulate you with hiring -Pegah-. What amazing customer service she provided to me today. Honestly, this was the best level of service I have ever received in any fast food. I can tell the level of customer service was in a level of a high end luxury dine in restaurants. There was a big mistake that happened at the drive thru by one of your employees and after I got to the payment window, I saw -Pegah- already there to make sure there is nothing to get mistaken, she actively listened and apologized to me for the mistake without me even get upset, so at the point that I found that I have been taken care of to get  the right food, I was even thinking about time, mistakes and getting angry. It was an amazing feeling I have received when I got taken care of not only for the money that I paid extra and the wrong sandwich, but she kindly provided me with free apple pie and asked me to keep the wrong sandwiches even though I didnt order them. As a long term manager in retail, I want to thank you (Mina) for getting amazing people like -Pegah- hired in your team and thank -Pegah- for her amazing service. I want to let you know that I just bought my items less than half an hour ago, but I found it will be so unfair to not mention this to everyone with this level of customer service. Thank you so much.
Mmmm, two dollar sundaes. How can you go wrong. I recommend adding both, hot fudge and caramel. Parking: Lots of parking.

A beautiful date atmosphere and destination. The train of destiny let my husband and I here. We joined a nice dinner at candlelight... or should I say CAMEL-LIGHT?? hahahhahahhahahHhahhha. The food? Exquisite and sludgy. We will be coming back soon, that is a promise.
Fast service. Clean dinning area. Good customer service. Clean washroom.
Fast and good service. He listens to you and gives you the right time for you. Thank you, Mc

Today the drive in was busy, but I parked and went in for take out.   I ordered an egg McMuffin  meal, on my phone.  When I went in, I  was the only person there.   My order was ready in about 2 minutes. I had it on the patio,  and with only 1 other person there, there were lots of tables available.  The food was fine, at McDonalds you always know what to expect. Very good
Very quick service. Order-taker and cashier extremely pleasant, and thanked us for waiting a couple minutes while he was taking another worker.
Fast and delicious. Ever since I was a kid.

This place is busy but always fast they have enough staff all the time and move things quickly they have the self ordering screens for inside and the drive through moves fairly quickly as they have two drive through (ordering lanes) entrances which helps the flow staff is smiling and the place is clean they also have a kids area Vegetarian options: They have salads there which helps the vegetarians also plant based burgers Dietary restrictions: They can make custom burgers for you if things need to be taken out Parking: Ample amount of parking Kid-friendliness: Always great for the kids Wheelchair accessibility: Parking and easy to move around in a wheelchair
prolly the best Mcdonald in the area Wheelchair accessibility: very nice Food : 5/5 |
This McDonalds is pretty fast. The drive thru is often full but moving good.

Shoutout to the Friday 2am team!! Food was fresh and tasty as always. The gentleman who worked the drive-thru window provided exceptional service. This location is, imo, the best McDs in all of Lower Mainland!!

Always a lineup but staff get you through pretty quick. First cheeseburger I have ordered in a long time. As soon as I saw it I remembered why I  dont  anymore.  I almost couldnt find the meat! If that is what it was!

Come here after the gym. Never got sick so thats good. Its not jammed packed like most McDonalds during lunch time. Usually get junior chicken with an extra patty cause my muscles need it you know. I like their team they are always in a good mood or at least are good actors/actresses. I will be back after my gym session!
Good location. The staffs works so hard and fast. If your order is late or wrong, its not because they didnt try.  Supper buys at time and I feel for the staffs.
Drive thru fast and efficient!

Its a nice looking McDonald, lots of seating space; Ive never seen it packed, but at the same time, its always busy.  Ive always had good service at this place, just be polite. Food is average Mc Donalds food, with breakfast menu in the morning.

Though there are always long lineups here the staff work at an exceptional speed, getting every order Ive ever placed right, and offer free drinks if it takes more than 5 minutes to make your meal. It is personally one of my favourite McDonalds

McDonalds has changed so much over the years that Ive lived here. I remember way back when the play place was on the west side of the restaurant in the early days.. and so much bulkier in size, too. The years pass, but the memories stay the same. Ive enjoyed many a meal here and have never stayed any longer than maybe 20 minutes at most, but, each time its always been a good experience. No order mistaken, no food tasting off or different than it should, always friendly. Its like any other McDonalds, sure, but this is the one I call mine.

Not just during Covid 19, but everytime we all concern about cleanliness, hygine and helpful staff MacDonald right on Barnet highway deserves 5 stars, everytime I visit they guys are helpful, and lovable towards kids, soft spoken and main concern is they are they take special care of hygiene. They could do even more better. But for now they are good. Cheers...

Great experience this morning, the young man by the name of RV was exceptional. He had such good energy, treated all customers with such respect and all with a smile and positive energy. He should be commended for his great service!

Staff was very friendly. I was looking for the garbage can and one employee offered to help take the garbage/tray for me. Ordered using their self serve kiosks and the ordered was processed quickly. The play place was a bit small and limited.
we enjoy the coffee and the lovely donuts there, and my kid enjoy the playground
One of the more friendly McDonalds staffs. Stephanie the manager is amazing and does a great job under extreme pressure. the place is kept clean and well maintained. Nice family atmosphere!
The surrounded space inside this restaurant for kids to play there was very useful idea.
This guys terninal machine broke! They proveded excellent service by continoue providing food . They know what it means to be hungry!

We are going to this Macdonalds in coquitlam on Barnet hwy for about 30 years and never had any problem, I think Its the best of all the other restaurants in tri cities. During coupon book days they let you keep the coupon for next time   and never charge for extra sauces  . Everyday I go there for my afternoon coffee. BEST COFFEE
Busy drive through but amazing food hot fries and excellent capabilities and services. Good for a cone or a burger if you need a quick snack.
Quality from drive-thru to kitchen to service. There is a reason this place is lined up out to the street on any given day. Food is correct, fresh, and fast.
Its usually not very busy in the mornings.

This the place to be when u want to avoid port moody Macdonald. The place always has at least 1 cashier as stand by, and a few order machine willing to take order from customer. Sometime there is a long line up to order the food. But they will accept all coupon from book, online , and MacDonald app. The staff are polite. And manager is ensure everything is OK when the order got delay. This location can seat up a lot of people, and there is a fun section for kids to play with. This is the 2nd best MacDonald in TriCity city area. Compare to port moody Macdonald, this MacDonald treat customer with smile and respect.
The customer service here is great, especially one of the girls with blonde hair and glasses. She always get my order perfect and is extremely friendly.
Probably my favourite location. Big, lots of seating, self-serve order screens arent crammed in a corner like an afterthought, comfy booths, and a 2 lane drive thru!

We have been going to this McDonakds on Barnet  for years and order sausage egg McMuffins with egg white only.  The front staff because it is a revolving process with staff sometimes mix the order up but if the Supervisor Tina is on staff that day they are  perfect.  She is always patient and professional with all the staff and assists them as they become more familiar with the ordering and use the ask function on the computer.   She also greets everyone with a smile and thank you.  McDonslds is very fortunate to have a dedicated employee like Tina....continued success to her in all her endeavors.....Susan and Dennis

Everybody saying its not actually 24 hours is wrong, (mostly) during the night their system updates, it takes about 20 minutes and theyre open again. If youre one of the unlucky few who come by during those 20 minutes then Im sorry but thats just the way the world works sometimes

Clean and busy. Not much parking. It is hard to get seats because theres lots of elderly people who sit there for hours. Update: Ordered fires and they were cold. Asked for a fresh batch and no questions were asked. Awesome customer service!
Went through the drive-thru for the first time at this location and I was thoroughly impressed by how quick and accurate the staff work.
At these days with Covid-19, washroom was up and running, and clean. Good friendly service too. Good system for customers in and out with regard to social distancy.
One of the well managed McD I have been to. Pleasantly clean and spacious.

On Saturday night (30 nov)  I visited Mc Donalds I got excellent service the person taking payment was so nice I really appreciate him he was manager but forget his name I think it was starting with the V letter he was serving guest so fast I really like that I am very big fan of Fast food
Staffs are polite, great service   highly recommended this place
Loved it as a kid, same love as an adult especially now that they have healthier choices, only regret is that they took away their salads.
Quick easy drive thru meals. Friendly staff for the most part Parking: Plenty available
Its a McDonalds. No problems. Consistent food. We go here all the time.
Delightful experience. Came for a double cheese after work and was joyed. Not only was it made to perfection but was also asked how my meal was after I sat done.
It was McDonalds and they are all pretty much the same. This one has great seating and lots of it
Its great but should have more workers. Things were slow when it comes to crowded in Mcdonalds.
Nice location. Lunch times can be busy but there waiting time isnt too bad
Plenty of seats at this restaurant! There s a kids play place too. The renovated place will make you stay longer!
insane drivethru lineups at night so bring playing cards and your appetite
Got my order right and it tasted great. What more can you ask for?
Nice and welcome service . Drop off around 2 times a week Food
I used to work here and overall it was a good job with good staff and good hours. Great as a worker or customer!
Its macdonalds...food good for what it is ..burgers fries coffee..milkshakes..nuggets. overall cheap place to eat something on the go ..
The place is clean and bigger than other places in Coquitlam. So its comfortable but playground inside is simpler than other branches.
Best service I ve had at mcdonald s so far
Quick sevice under trying times with some inpatient  clients.we always sit outside  and enjoy our food in peace.
My order took so long and I was the only one in the dang place
Grabbed a $1.00 cone for summer! Lots of self checkout! But I was paying cash so had to wait in line.
Fast and hot. What you would expect from a McDonalds.
I always enjoy my visit to the McDonalds on the Barnet hwy every one is friendly & its most efficient one Ive ever been in.
Amazing service. The server remember me and my girlfriend even tho we dont come here that often.
Great that its open til eleven. Food good as usual. Please serve Oreo milkshakes!!
Amazing location! The staff is super friendly. Every visit is a pleasure. Keep it up!
Too much line up on drive thru...but was being tackled very professionally
I always get large double double...Tania makes fun of me about that, lol.
This location is legendary. Drive thru is super quick and the staff are efficient to the tee
Very busy location . Order comes out correct 98% of the time
Very impressed at the hard work sanitizing and keeping staff and diners safe.
Drive thru was quick coffee is real tasty
Fast, friendly and respectful service in the drive thru.
Everything was fresh and the bathroom didnt smell like pee lol
Used the app it worked great.  The Mcgriddle was delicious
The fries were very hot and salty and the service was fast
Always fast service. We had a new person and did fairly well
Sometimes,  usually with kids.
Good
Its a good establishment. Loved to go to the play place when I was younger
I like my vanilla  lattes  and sausage muffin in the morning. Its a nice McDonald to go to.
Big, safe atmosphere with friendly, efficient staff. The poutine is excellent.
One of the better McDonalds I regularly use.
We buy  Create your own burger and I was amazing and the personal was very nice
Love the coffee! Quick and fast service! Good coffee for a good deal!
Always quick, friendly and pretty decent fries every time.
It has a small play place,w which is nice to kids. A lot of seats and even outdoor seats.
This resturant was clean. The burgers were fresh. Friendly team too!
It is big enough and has outdoor tables for seating.
We always go here late at night for cravings.  always fresh and very nice crews :)
MacDonalds delivers exactly what they promise. Consistently.
My favourite McDonald s in the lower mainland. Foods perfect 9 times out of 10.
Long lineup but but very courteous staff
Busy location, quick and friendly service for how busy it is. Will be back again
Convenient location, nice and clean environment, love the drive through service
Pretty good service and the staffs are very nice to all customers.
